# notify.env.example -- template for the OPTIONAL alert-delivery hook.
#
# The real file lives ON THE HOST at /srv/monitoring/notify.env and is NEVER
# committed to the repo (it contains a webhook URL, which is secret-adjacent:
# anyone holding it can post to your notification channel).
#
# Activation flow:
#   1. ssh root@<droplet-ip>
#   2. umask 077; printf 'NOTIFY_WEBHOOK_URL=%s\n' '<your webhook url>' \
#        > /srv/monitoring/notify.env
#   3. re-run setup-monitoring.sh from your workstation (see the README).
#      The script renders a Grafana webhook contact point ("sakana-notify")
#      plus a notification policy routing severity=page and severity=ticket
#      alerts to it, then restarts Grafana. The URL is never echoed and lands
#      only in a root:grafana 640 provisioning file.
#
# Deactivation: delete /srv/monitoring/notify.env and re-run the script --
# the rendered provisioning files are removed and alerts go back to UI-only.
# (See the README "Deprovisioning notifications" note about grafana.db.)
#
# Format rules: exactly KEY=VALUE, no quotes, no spaces around '='.
# Any https endpoint that accepts a POSTed JSON body works (a self-hosted
# webhook bridge, a chat-service incoming webhook, ntfy, etc.).
NOTIFY_WEBHOOK_URL=
